welcomeToYJOZ: Welcome to YJOZ. Before using , please carefully review the following Terms and Conditions, as they govern the contractual relationship between you  and YJOZ.
YJOZPlatformIntro: YJOZ is a platform that allows:
YJOZOwnersDescription: (a) users to advertise items for rent (such users being 'owners').
YJOZRenterCommunication: (b) owners to communicate with, and enter into rental arrangements with other users (such users who borrow are referred to as 'renters').
YJOZRenterPayment: (c) renters to pay owners for renting the relevant items;
YJOZDisputeResolution: (d) users to resolve disputes concerning the rented items, which we make available to you through the YJOZ application available for download on your mobile device called 'YJOZ App'.
YJOZSocialFeaturesIntro: 2.1 We may, from time-to-time, provide social features on the YJOZ Platform that enable you to message and share information about your use of the YJOZ Platform with other users.
YJOZAcceptableUseCompliance: 2.2 Any use of these social features should comply with our Rules of Acceptable Use below.
CreateAccountRequirements: 3.1 In order to use the YJOZ Platform, you must:
CreateAccountStepA: (a) Create an account using your email address (your "Account").
CreateAccountStepB: (b) Establish a password for your account. We recommend that you use "strong" passwords (passwords that contain a mix of upper and lower case letters, digits, and symbols) with your account.
AgeRequirement: 3.2 You must be 18 years of age or older and capable of entering into a legally binding agreement to use the YJOZ Platform. If you are under the age of 18, we may require a parent or guardian to enter into the agreement on your behalf. In this instance, we will enter into a legally binding agreement with the parent or guardian.
AccountResponsibility: 3.3 You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your login details and for any activities that occur under your account. If you have any concerns that your account may have been misused, you should contact us at info@yjoz.com right away to let us know.

RulesOfAcceptableUseIntro: 10.1 In addition to the other requirements within these Terms and Conditions, this section describes specific rules that apply to your use of the YJOZ Platform (the 'Rules of Acceptable Use').

Rule4: (d) Advocate, promote, or engage in any illegal or unlawful conduct or conduct that causes theft, loss, damage, or injury to any person or property.
Rule5: (e) Promote or advertise any goods or services other than items you, as a owner, make available for rent through the YJOZ Platform.

Rule7: (g) Modify, interfere with, intercept, disrupt, or hack the YJOZ Platform.

Rule9: (i) Collect any data from the YJOZ Platform other than in accordance with these Terms and Conditions.
Rule10: (j) Submit or contribute any user content that contains nudity or violence or is abusive, threatening, obscene, misleading, untrue, or offensive.
Rule11: (k) Submit or contribute any user content that you do not own or have the right to use or otherwise infringe the copyright, trademark, or other rights of third parties.
Rule12: (l) Use any user content in violation of any licensing terms specified by the owner.
Rule13: (m) Other than leaving reviews about owners or items, submit or contribute any information or commentary about another person without that person's permission.
Rule14: (n) Threaten, abuse, or invade another's privacy, or cause annoyance, inconvenience, or needless anxiety, or be likely to harass, upset, embarrass, alarm, or annoy any other person (including but not limited to other users and YJOZ employees).
Rule15: (o) Use any automated system, including without limitation 'robots,' 'spiders,' or 'offline readers,' to access the YJOZ Platform in a manner that sends more request messages to the YJOZ Platform than a human can reasonably produce in the same period of time.
Rule16: (p) Enter into any agreement to rent or rent any item other than through the YJOZ platform with any other user whom you initially met through the YJOZ Platform. Doing so is 'fee avoidance,' and you will be liable for double the fees avoided or an AED200 fine (whichever is more) for each instance of doing so.

heroParagraph: YJOZ, an innovative mobile application, is leading the change in reshaping the rental landscape in the UAE. Serving as a comprehensive marketplace, it empowers individuals and businesses to list a diverse range of rental items and services. Positioned as the pioneering sustainable brand in the GCC and Middle East, YJOZ specializes in delivering rental services with a clear focus on waste reduction and item reuse. By actively promoting a circular economy, YJOZ seeks to minimize the environmental impact of excessive consumption. YJOZ sets a precedent for sustainable practices, inspiring individuals and businesses to embrace eco-friendly approaches by highlighting the advantages of renting over traditional ownership. Through this, YJOZ contributes to creating a more sustainable and environmentally friendly society in the GCC and Middle East.
